\end_inset

 stand for the input patterns and each value ti represents the actual output for pattern 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{i}$
\end_inset

.
 The proposed method in practice uses the mean classification error on the training set as the fitness measure,
 since the output of the produced model is one of the available categories of the dataset under study.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
End For
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Application of Genetic Operations.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Selection procedure.
 The remaining are substituted by chromosomes produced during crossover and mutation.
 The top 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{s}\times N_{c}$
\end_inset

 chromosomes are directly carried over to the next generation,
 while the rest are replaced by chromosomes generated through crossover and mutation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Crossover procedure.
 This procedure produces new chromosomes from the current population.
 For every pair 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(c_{1},c_{2}\right)$
\end_inset

 of new chromosomes two chromosomes denoted as 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{1}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{2}$
\end_inset

 are selected from the current population using tournament selection.
 The production of 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(c_{1},c_{2}\right)$
\end_inset

 will be performed using one - point crossover 
\shape italic

\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Poli 1998"
literal "false"

\end_inset


\shape default
.
 An example of this procedure is outlined in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "fig:A-graphical-example"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Mutation procedure.
 Draw a random number 
\begin_inset Formula $r\le1$
\end_inset

 for each element of every chromosome.
 Alter randomly this element when 
\begin_inset Formula $r\le p_{m}$
\end_inset

.
 The mutation procedure is depicted as a flowchart in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "fig:The-flowchart-of"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Termination check step.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Set 
\begin_inset Formula $k=k+1$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
If 
\begin_inset Formula $k<N_{g}$
\end_inset

 then go to Fitness calculation step else go to Testing step.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Testing step.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Get the best chromosome 
\begin_inset Formula $c^{*}$
\end_inset

 of the population with the lowest fitness value and create the corresponding classification program 
\begin_inset Formula $G^{*}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Apply the classification program to the test set of the objective problem and calculate the corresponding test error.
 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
